	This document provides detailed instructions on how to run the Part 4 of our IRWA project.

	o How to run the code
	
	This code is written in python hence it must be executed in any pyhton-supported workframes. As a reference, we have done ourproject in Visual Studio Code

	Our project is based on the following files of data: Rus_Ukr_war_data.json.

  o To download this repository locally open a terminal console and execute:

  ```
  cd <your preferred projects root directory>
  
  ```

  o To run the web app --> python web_app.py
  o The following information will appear in the terminal:

    * Serving Flask app 'web_app', 
    * Debug mode: on
        WARNING: This is a development server. Do not use it in a production deployment. Use a production WSGI server instead.
    * Running on all addresses (0.0.0.0)
    * Running on http://127.0.0.1:8088
    * Running on http://192.168.1.232:8088

  o Open the web app in your Browser by clicking on of the above links

  o Some installs may be needed such as:

    * pip install httpagentparser
    * pip install Flask pandas nltk faker
    * pip3 install virtualenv

  

  

	
